sentence_chunk: February 20, 2025 Dear Hiring Team, I am writing to apply for the Research Engineer / Research Scientist (Multimodal) role at Anthropic. With a background in multimodal AI, large language models, and information retrieval, I am excited about the opportunity to contribute to Anthropicâ€™s mission of developing safe, interpretable, and scalable AI systems. I recently completed my MSc in Human-Computer Interaction from the University of Birmingham, where my research focused on GraphMinds, a project integrating large language models with structured and multimodal data such as text, images, and graphs to improve retrieval-augmented generation and explainability. My academic and professional work has been centered around building scalable AI architectures, fine-tuning language models, and optimizing knowledge retrieval. As a Research Associate at the University of Birmingham, I worked on agentic machine learning pipelines that enabled language models to reason with complex data structures, including text, diagrams, and knowledge graphs, leading to improvements in retrieval accuracy. I also optimized large-scale data processing using Ray, Dask, and GPU acceleration to ensure efficient multimodal analysis. During my tenure as an AI Intern at Our Time HQ, I fine-tuned transformer-based natural language processing models, built ETL pipelines, and conducted human-in-the-loop evaluations to refine AI-driven responses. At MICxN Lab, my work in reinforcement learning for sequential decision-making involved handling multimodal datasets such as GPS tracking and traffic simulations, strengthening my ability to work across different data modalities. Beyond research, I have practical experience in language model fine-tuning, retrieval architectures, AI safety techniques, and high-performance computing, all of which are critical to developing robust and scalable AI systems. What excites me most about Anthropic is your commitment to AI safety, multimodal research, and large-scale empirical AI development.

Your focus on trustworthy and steerable AI systems strongly aligns with my work and research interests. I would love the opportunity to be part of your team and contribute my expertise in multimodal learning, retrieval models, and AI robustness. Please find my CV attached for your review. I look forward to discussing further. Best regards, Tirth Kanani
